<!---------------------------->
<table cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Recommended Level<br>for starting quest:</b></td><td valign="bottom"> 45<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting zone:</b></td><td valign="top"> Eastern Wastes<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Additional zones:</b></td><td valign="top"> --<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting NPC:</b></td><td valign="top"> Garadain Glacierbane<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Reward:</b></td><td valign="top"> Fifth Coldain Ring (Obsidian)<br><br></td></tr>
</table>

This is the fifth part in the ten part series of Coldain Ring Quests. You do not have to do any of the earlier parts in order to do this entire part, except for the turn in at the end. This one you will need a strong partner to do.<br>
<br>
Your first goal is to kill a RyGorr Messanger.  He's very easy to kill, but rather rare.  He drops 'RyGorr Invasion Plans' which are droppable, so it's usually pretty easy to find some for sale for less than 50pp if you don't want to waste your time looking for him.<br>
<br>
Once you have the plans, give them to 'a Coldain Lookout' slightly East of Garadain's camp.  If he had been looking west, he might have seen the invasion force, but the fool looked the wrong way.  Stupid dwarves.<br>
<br>
As soon as you hand him the plans, Scarbrow Ga'Hruk immediately spawns about 100 paces east of the camp.  With him, spawn several RyGorr invaders and several oracles of RyGorr.  There are several things you can do now, the easiest option is to be high enough level (around 55 should easily be safe, at 61 it was cake) person single pull him from the pack, then kill him.  The rest of the pack will still wipe out Garadain's camp, so you will have to wait half an hour for the camp to respawn.  The other way to do it, is to wait a few moments, when I was doing this, the Invaders ran in first leaving Scarbrow and 2 oracles at the spawn point.  From there you can pull Scarbrow and the Oracles.  The Oracles will probably be casting on themselves or on you, so get out of range, or wait for their spells to hit before you FD.  If you can time it right, this will make it easy to split Scarbrow off of them.  You and your partner should then be able to fear-kite Scarbrow pretty easily.  If you already have Harmshield, you might want to throw that up early to absorb his Harm Touch.<br>
<br>
When killed, Scarbrow will always drop his head, and occasionally will also drop a Frozen Orb.  The Frozen Orb is droppable and a pretty good caster range item.<br>
<br>
When the Coldain camp respawns, hand Garadain your platinum ring and Scarbrow's head to receive your Obsidian Coldain Insignia Ring.<br>
<br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP  <br>
AC: +5 Str: +5 Magic Resist: +5  <br>
Weight: 0.1 <br>
Classes: All <br>
Races: All  <br>
Slot: Finger<br><br>

